SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1239
By Bailey
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Natalie Saxon-Adams for
her meritorious service to the State of
Tennessee.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those estimable public servants who have dedicated themselves to
improving the quality of life for their fellow citizens; and
WHEREAS, Natalie Saxon-Adams is one such estimable person, who evinces the
greatest integrity and probity in all her chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, a native of Hendersonville, Mrs. Saxon-Adams launched her distinguished
career with the Cookeville-Putnam County Chamber of Commerce on February 7, 2022; and
WHEREAS, Natalie Saxon-Adams was promoted to membership manager in October
2022 and successfully led the membership department through two managerial maternity
leaves, earning the respect and admiration of her colleagues and community alike for the
superior quality of her work; and
WHEREAS, during her tenure, Mrs. Saxon-Adams has spearheaded 282 ribbon-cutting
ceremonies and nineteen school adoption ceremonies, assisted with 118 events, and welcomed
315 new members into the Chamber; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Saxon-Adams was a server lead and bartender at Seven Senses Food
and Cheer for five years before joining the Chamber and was there a total of seven years; and
WHEREAS, a 2026 graduate of Leadership Putnam, Natalie Saxon-Adams earned a
Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration with a concentration in Marketing from
Tennessee Technological University in 2020; and
WHEREAS, a woman of many talents and passions, Mrs. Saxon-Adams has a deep
love for music, animals, and Cookeville's historic Westside; and
SJR1239
018436
- 1 -

WHEREAS, her many professional accomplishments aside, Natalie Saxon-Adams is
most grateful for the love and support she shares with her husband, Jeff, with whom she
welcomed her first son, Avery, in January 2025; and
WHEREAS, the success of the State of Tennessee, the strength of our communities,
and the overall vitality of our society depend, in great measure, on the dedication of people such
as Mrs. Saxon-Adams, who use their considerable talents and resources to serve others; and
WHEREAS, Natalie Saxon-Adams is wholly committed to the noble precepts of public
service that have earned Tennessee recognition as the Volunteer State, and she should be
specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Natalie Saxon-Adams for
her indelible contributions to Putnam County and the State of Tennessee and extend to her our
best wishes for much continued success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
